The paper describes a machine translation system using convolutional sequence to sequence architectures, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, cs.CL is the most likely sub-category. The use of additional data obtained through backtranslation involves techniques from artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML), making cs.AI and cs.LG likely sub-categories as well. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) is a common technique in computer vision (CV), which could make cs.CV a possible sub-category. Finally, the use of neural networks for machine translation could also fall under the category of neural networks (NE), making it a possible sub-category.
